About 11 persons who have contact with the index case of COVID-19 in Ondo State have been placed on isolation at the Army’s Owena Barracks in Akure. Ondo Commissioner for Health, Dr Wahab Adegbenro, who disclosed this yesterday, said the first and only Coronavirus case is a military officer. Dr. Adegbenro said the index case was in stable condition and responding to treatment. Adegbenro stated that the patient’s wife, son and nine health officers as well as colleagues have been under isolation. He said two suspected cases of COVID-19 have been sent to Lagos for testing.